<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5396] DRDAStatement and DRDAConnThread swallow IOExceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5396</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DRDAConnThread.closeStream():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	} catch (IOException e) &lt;/p&gt;
{
	    Util.javaException(e);
	    
	}

&lt;p&gt;DRDAStatement.execute():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;		} catch (IOException e) &lt;/p&gt;
{ 
			Util.javaException(e);
		}

&lt;p&gt;Since Util.javaException() only returns an exception, this code doesn&apos;t work as intended. The returned exception should also be thrown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
